[32m│[0m Excellent finding! When I URL-encode the angle brackets (`%3C` and `%3E`),   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the filter decodes them but then strips out the `<script>` tags, leaving     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m only `alert(1)` reflected in the HTML.                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Analysis Summary                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **detailed_summary**                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I tested XSS payloads on the `/page` endpoint with various encoding          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m techniques to understand how the filter works:                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Unencoded HTML tags** (`<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>`):             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Filter detects and truncates the payload                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Only `<img` is reflected, rest is stripped                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Returns "error_star.png" (failed state)                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **URL-encoded payload**                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (`%3Cimg%20src%3Dx%20onerror%3Dalert%28%27XSS%27%29%3E`):                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Filter detects the encoded dangerous content                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Nothing is reflected in the HTML                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Returns "new_star.png" (initial/blocked state)                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Double URL-encoded** (`%253Cscript%253E...`):                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - First layer decoded by server                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Second layer (`%3Cscript%3E`) reflected as-is (still encoded, harmless) [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Returns "error_star.png" (failed state)                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **URL-encoded brackets only** (`%3Cscript%3Ealert(1)%3C/script%3E`):      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Server decodes `%3C` → `<` and `%3E` → `>`                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Filter strips out `<script>` and `</script>` tags                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Only `alert(1)` is reflected                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Returns "error_star.png" (failed state)                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Filter behavior**: The application has a multi-layer XSS filter that:      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Detects raw HTML tags and blocks/truncates them                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Decodes URL-encoded input before filtering                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Strips dangerous tags like `<script>`, `<img>` after decoding              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Shows different error states based on what's detected                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **URL encoding does NOT bypass the filter** - it gets decoded before the     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m filter is applied.                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
